   <text>
      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Royal Exchange ¶ Adelaide 27th August 1890 ¶ Baron Von Mueller KCMG Ph D MD &amp;c &amp;c &amp;c &amp;c ¶ President Royal Geographical Society ¶ Melbourne...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">90.08.27a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From David Lindsay</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">ML MSS.200/1, item 2, letter book, pp. 423-5, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Royal Exchange</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Adelaide 27th August 1890</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Baron Von Mueller KCMG Ph D MD &amp;c &amp;c &amp;c &amp;c</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">President Royal Geographical Society</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[…]<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">One or<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">two</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>lines</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">, including the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">salutation</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">,</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>illegible</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>— letter book copy smudged. All […] in the following text refer to illegible words or lines.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Leader of the exploration in Australia of which Sir Thos Elder has so generously offered to bear the cost.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Elder Scientific Exploring Expedition, 1891-2.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Lindsay’s application was successful; see Lindsay (1893)<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>for his journal of the expedition.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I do so with considerable confidence when I call to mind the correspondence which has passed between your branch of the Geographical Society and myself re exploring the North West country.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I may be permitted to enumerate the qualities which make me competent for such a position.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I […] am in perfect health having been fully accepted as a "first class life" by the Doctor of the A.M.P.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Australian Mutual Provident.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Society.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>My courage endurance and energy have been shown on the works I have done in the past. Being by profession a Surveyor I am able to map down the country with accuracy, and the experience of fifteen (15) years in the active practice of my profession as a Surveyor and Explorer qualifies me to report accurately on the topography and geography of the country passed over.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have a fair practical knowledge of minerals. I do not claim to be a botanist or geologist although of the latter science I have a sufficient knowledge to enable me to describe the rock formations — But here I might be allowed to suggest, that the second in command should be a Geologist with a knowledge of mineralogy and botany attention to which branches of the work would occupy a mans full time —</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The exploration of Arnhem land shows that I am able to deal successfully with the natives no matter how troublesome they may be.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>When Lindsay explored Arnhem Land for<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the Government of SA in 1883,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>his party survived attacks by Aborigines, one group of which numbered 300 (<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">ADB</seg>, vol. 10, p. 106).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am, as you know, thoroughly intimate with the Country from South to North having spent about 7 years in tropical Australia and having twice crossed the continent; besides spending about nine months in Central Australia prospecting and surveying.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have done much work with Camels and have a very good knowledge of those animals.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>When exploring in 1886 I discovered the "Australian Ruby" and also reported that gold would be found.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[…] field south of the [Hale] River now being worked was discovered during the same journey [west] of the country near the [McArthur River I wrote that [Felspar] silver, lead and probably gold would be found […] deposit of lead and silver ores were discovered and worked.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Being […] to yourself and the members of the Council of the R G Society I feel that […]</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>If I am […] and […] will devote my best energies and [intents] to the successful completion of the very important work proposed.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Trusting that my application will be favorably received</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your Obedt Servant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>David Lindsay</p>
         </div>
      </body>
   </text>
